600 1592 654 (Do facet gets/puts throw on error?) 654 SB
300 1641 163 (Sections:) 163 SB
600 1641 186 (22 \(many\)) 186 SB
300 1690 125 (Status:) 125 SB
600 1690 110 (active) 110 SB
300 1788 228 (Description:) 228 SB
600 1837 1496 (When a facet member get or put identifies an error, it is documented as setting a) 1496 SB
600 1886 1363 (bit in its "ios_type" argument's iostate. In iostream, when this happens an) 1363 SB
600 1935 1451 (exception is thrown if the corresponding bit is set in the exception state.  Does) 1451 SB
600 1984 1473 (an exception get thrown under the same circumstances in locale functions? The) 1473 SB
600 2033 384 (Draft is inconsistent.) 384 SB
300 2082 213 (Discussion:) 213 SB
600 2131 1497 (If the locale doesn't throw, iostreams must check the error state itself and throw;) 1497 SB
600 2180 1177 (if locale throws, iostream probably needs to catch and rethrow.) 1177 SB
300 2229 398 (Proposed Resolution:) 398 SB
600 2278 172 (A choice:) 172 SB
600 2376 981 (1. Locale members throw if the exception bit says so.) 981 SB
600 2425 958 (2. Locale members don't throw, the only set iostate.) 958 SB
600 2523 909 (I don't know which is better, but I lean toward 1.) 909 SB
300 2572 200 (Requestor:) 200 SB
300 2621 140 (Owner:) 140 SB
